-- Ecuador's Correa Vows Not to Negotiate, Thanks Security Forces for Rescue
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l   a n d   H e l e n   M u r p h y
-- 2010-10-01T02:53:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/ecuador-s-correa-vows-not-to-negotiate-with-police-after-army-rescues-him.html
Ecuadorean President Rafael Correa
thanked security forces for rescuing him from a hospital
besieged by police protesting a government plan to reduce their
wages.  “We will never cede, we will never negotiate,” Correa
said from a balcony at the presidential palace minutes after a
gunfight that freed him.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
